@hypothesis_correction Original Sub-N hypothesis: "docker integrations cause nexus kick tree to silently emit 0 bytes on ubu1 (output swallowed by docker container)". Post-retirement evidence: ubu1 `nexus kick tree` STILL emits 0 bytes after shim removal — so the docker shim was NOT the proximate cause of the empty output. The true ubu1 root cause is upstream in run.hexa kick-subcommand dispatch. Airgenome retirement still correct (the shim was confirmed-unused dead code routing through a container that may not even be running on hetzner per shim's own header note `htz: bind mount 없음 — 제외 대상`).

